This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

Interesting, this seem to be fixed by Ruby 2.3.1.
@Jun, could you please investigate this?
Vit, yes I will investigate this later.

Created attachment 1158243 Update to v1.0.2 to fix test suite for Ruby 2.3.0 compatibility
*High light*
I updated the version to latest v1.0.2, that is including the fix for ruby 2.3.0. [1] I also moved README.md to "%files doc".
[1] https://github.com/typhoeus/typhoeus/commit/8b61442
*Package dependency*
The dependency is no problem.
+ dnf repoquery --enablerepo=rawhide --whatrequires 'rubygem(typhoeus)' => No result
+ dnf repoquery --enablerepo=rawhide --whatrequires 'rubygem-typhoeus' rubygem-typhoeus-doc-0:0.7.2-1.fc23.noarch
+ dnf repoquery --enablerepo=rawhide-source --arch src --whatrequires 'rubygem(typhoeus)' rubygem-oauth-0:0.4.7-9.fc24.src gem spec: ok, rpm spec: ok rubygem-webmock-0:1.21.0-1.fc24.src gem spec: ok, rpm spec: ok
+ dnf repoquery --enablerepo=rawhide-source --arch src --whatrequires 'rubygem-typhoeus' => No result
Could you check this patch file? Thanks.

Hi Jun, I approved you in PkgDB, so feel free to push the changes.
One minor nit though. Since you are not doing anything special to fix this bug, IOW the fix is part of the rebase, I would not mention it in Changelog. But that might be just my POV, so use your best judgment ;)
